@mheon There are some warnings built into opencontainers/selinux to prevent user attempts to relabel system directories.

```
	exclude_paths := map[string]bool{"/": true, "/usr": true, "/etc": true, "/tmp": true, "/home": true, "/run": true, "/var": true, "/root": true}
	if exclude_paths[path] {
		return fmt.Errorf("SELinux relabeling of %s is not allowed", path)
	}
```

@najamelan if you're running on centos7, I suggest using this package:
https://trunk.rdoproject.org/centos7-master/deps/latest/x86_64/podman-1.0.0-3.git921f98f.el7.x86_64.rpm

Which contains a tested version of podman, which shouldn't have this bug anymore.
